# Docker build-context ignore for this service's Dockerfile.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: .gitignore has NO effect on `docker COPY`. Docker only
# consults .dockerignore files. When the build context is the repo root, a
# `COPY integrations/fabri /repo/integrations/fabri` would otherwise bake the
# deployer's own .env (their OPENAI/GEMINI API keys), their local .venv, and
# runs/ (uploaded user videos, execution traces, sqlite memory) straight into a
# shareable image — leaking secrets and private user data to anyone the image
# is pushed/shared to.
#
# BuildKit reads `<Dockerfile>.dockerignore` (i.e. Dockerfile.dockerignore)
# when building with this specific Dockerfile. BuildKit is already required for
# the named build context, so this per-Dockerfile ignore is honored and keeps
# secrets and local state out of both the image and the context upload.
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.venv
**/runs
**/.runs
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
apps
packages
.git
